    "docHtml": "<p>A two-handed wooden hammer with a broad, flat head and long haft, the maul is built for siege work and breach-fighting. In a warrior's grip, it crashes through door-timbers, shield-walls, and armored shoulders alike. Heavy enough to require both hands and the full weight of a man's charge, it is the choice of the assault engineer and the hill-fort berserker.</p>\n",
